body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, my name is Kyle Allen and I'm from Smart Data Solutions. May I ask for your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Nicole. Could you please provide me with your date of birth, with each number spelled out?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my date of birth is zero three slash zero seven slash one nine eight nine.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Nicole. Can you also confirm the first four digits of your phone number, spelling each digit out as well?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, the first four digits of my phone number are nine four zero two.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for sharing that information, Nicole. Is there anything else you'd like to provide or discuss today?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great to hear! Thank you for your time, Nicole. Have a wonderful day!
